to User Guide and Admin User Guide

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-19 22:04:43.000000000', 'message': 'libvirt: Fix infinite loop waiting for block job

Libvirt may return an empty dict when a block job has completed.
In this case, _wait_for_block_job will return True, causing
its callers to loop.

Affects volume_snapshot_delete, swap_volume, and live_snapshot.

(See http://libvirt.org/git/?p=libvirt.git;a=commit;h=0f9e67bf )

Closes-Bug: #1260123
Change-Id: Iab81299f0ce32a14e46aee0fd389ed29f7e503b8

commit_message:
libvirt: Fix infinite loop waiting for block job

Libvirt may return an empty dict when a block job has completed.
In this case, _wait_for_block_job will return True, causing
its callers to loop.

Affects volume_snapshot_delete, swap_volume, and live_snapshot.

(See http://libvirt.org/git/?p=libvirt.git;a=commit;h=0f9e67bf )

Closes-Bug: #1260123
Change-Id: Iab81299f0ce32a14e46aee0fd389ed29f7e503b8

[{'created': '2014-01-09 01:27:01.000000000', 'message': 'Warn if read_affinity is configured but not enabled

To get the proxy's read affinity to work, you have to set both
"read_affinity = <stuff>" and "sorting_method = affinity" in the proxy
config. If you set the first but not the second, then you don't get
read affinity, and Swift doesn't help you determine why not.

Now the proxy will emit a warning message if read_affinity is set but
sorting_method is a value other than "affinity", so if you check your
logs to see why it isn't working, you'll get a hint.

Note that the message comes out twice per proxy process, so with 2
workers you'll see the warning 6 times on startup (2 for master + 2 *
2 per worker). It's sort of annoying, but at least it's not
per-request.

Bonus docstring fix: remove a sentence that's not true

Change-Id: Iad37d4979a1b7c45c0e3d1b83336dbcf7a68a0c9
'}]
commit_message:
Warn if read_affinity is configured but not enabled

To get the proxy's read affinity to work, you have to set both
"read_affinity = <stuff>" and "sorting_method = affinity" in the proxy
config. If you set the first but not the second, then you don't get
read affinity, and Swift doesn't help you determine why not.

Now the proxy will emit a warning message if read_affinity is set but
sorting_method is a value other than "affinity", so if you check your
logs to see why it isn't working, you'll get a hint.

Note that the message comes out twice per proxy process, so with 2
workers you'll see the warning 6 times on startup (2 for master + 2 *
2 per worker). It's sort of annoying, but at least it's not
per-request.

Bonus docstring fix: remove a sentence that's not true

Change-Id: Iad37d4979a1b7c45c0e3d1b83336dbcf7a68a0c9

commit_message:
Fix pip install failure due to missing nvp.ini file

It looks like sdist does not support symlinks, therefore
letting nvp.ini point to nsx.ini is not a good solution.
Since nvp.ini is going away, leave a copy for now, but
add a warning so that users are aware of the switch,
whilst preserving full backward-compatibility.

Closes-bug: #1266555

Change-Id: Id98c41145712583072a8e63a5de31ecc1074e420

commit_message:
Support the Event API

This patch adds support for the currently available
Event API, including events, event types, and traits.

Add an optional data type to the query, ex:
   ceilometer list-events -q 'hostname=string::localhost"

bp extend-client-operations

Change-Id: Icea9bd67f8ee4ff2bf9da9ff6894218689580eb3

changed

commit_message:
gitignore: add .localrc.auto and local.conf

The changeset of 893e66360caf3bcf0578d4541b3c17d089c33b02,
Change-Id of I367cadc86116621e9574ac203aafdab483d810d3
introduced local.conf and generates .localrc.auto.
But they aren't in .gitignore. This patch adds them into .gitignore.

Change-Id: I7d4dc99d980d9c5b5156cf915646bc96163a3dc4
Closes-Bug: #1267027

[{'created': '2014-01-07 19:10:37.000000000', 'message': 'Refactor keystone_user_role to be lazier

Currently, the entire list of user roles are
cached ASAP. Trying to pre-determine these
is very slow b/c there is no user role list
command in keystone, so you must iterate through
all tenant/user combinations to retrieve the list.

This patch makes the retrieval of all state info
lazy.

Partial-Bug: 1224179
Change-Id: I80a85f3ddf2c41fe447df5682ad31ac4df8f8b59
(cherry picked from commit a0a359801e7248b24d15b3acef3b398d5a2fb65f)
'}]
commit_message:
Refactor keystone_user_role to be lazier

Currently, the entire list of user roles are
cached ASAP. Trying to pre-determine these
is very slow b/c there is no user role list
command in keystone, so you must iterate through
all tenant/user combinations to retrieve the list.

This patch makes the retrieval of all state info
lazy.

Partial-Bug: 1224179
Change-Id: I80a85f3ddf2c41fe447df5682ad31ac4df8f8b59
(cherry picked from commit a0a359801e7248b24d15b3acef3b398d5a2fb65f)

commit_message:
Consolidate VM creation into devtest_setup.sh.

To run CI tests we have to use predefined baremetal nodes rather than
creating them during the test script - they might be real hardware, or
the virtual test clusters. Separating out creation from use also
permits tweaking the test VMs by hand, which can be a useful debugging
feature.

Change-Id: I698841b7beb4a2f847405664f46805ea7be4dc53

commit_message:
Move all devtest actions into child scripts.

This makes it possible to use them independently rather than running
the entire devtest all at once. There are other changes we might want
to do to the scripts, but since there is a lot of text moving I've
been conservative - we can do other changes in subsequent patches.

Change-Id: I6522d9443bcdbc1ae16b485ae3b9d8e547a6022f

commit_message:
API to check the requested power state

API to make a sanity check on the requested power state, before the API
was just passing whatever state requested by the user via RPC to the
conductor and it would fail there in case the state request wasn't valid,
giving a late feedback to the user and wasting resources.

As the same check is done on the provision method, a new exception was
created to reuse the exception message.

The patch also update the docstrings of the power() and provision()
methods to reflect the exceptions they might raise.

Change-Id: I47f957f738ef922b01b2c604180d8b6efe20ce8c

commit_message:
Sync config module from oslo

Add 'config' to openstack-common so that it syncs from Oslo,
move tools/conf -> tools/config to be able to sync from Oslo,
and then sync the changes which are proposed in oslo-incubator
commit Iee6cc05cad70963f2a151f595ac376c9338f5774.

Change-Id: I32a80b0e2aa0e26b9fc78b7546c07e102639374e

commit_message:
VMWare: session handling refactor

This is a suggested refactor for how the driver manages
its vSphere sessions. It optimises session reuse and
avoids evicting sessions from vCenter by unilateral use
of the Session Manager object.

commit_message:
Add env var to set network ranges used by tests

Adds
 POOL_DEFAULT which will set the value for all other networks if not
  defined
 POOL_ADMIN, POOL_PUBLIC, POOL_MANAGEMENT, POOL_PRIVATE, POOL_STORAGE which will set their respective network ranges.

This is needed so that test setups can easily have seperate network ranges
 so external routing can be controlled.

Closes-bug #1266539

Change-Id: I38168d52e959051530f2d18329d7241e9e0e47fa

commit_message:
Flush tokens in batches with DB2

When there is a very large number of expired tokens to be flushed,
keystone-manage token_flush will fail with DB2 because it fills
the transaction log. This fix causes tokens to be flushed with DB2 in
batches of 100 at a time to prevent the transaction log from
filling up.

Closes-Bug: #1257323
Change-Id: Ic57d8795a995462fc277ec9655eca9b460ffcbee

commit_message:
Add security service DB model and API.

Add support for managing security services information.

User will be able to create description for services
such as ldap, kerberos and active directory.
Security service record will contain type of service
(kerberos, ldap or ad), ip address of dns server, security
service server hostname or ip, domain, sid (security identifier)
and other auxiliary data.

Partially implements bp: join-tenant-network

Change-Id: I50e1f96496a40840aad97b77024a11302a1dd997

commit_message:
Adds misc options

This change adds support for miscellaneous options to be set.
Things that haven't been added as attributes, or specifically,
third party additions that don't belong in stackforge (e.g. cobalt)

Change-Id: Ibea4076b4e715cec6d2eaf5ac71c36aebf2957d7

(1 inline comment)

Why not make this config option more consistent with the other OVS-related config options used by the various agents by putting it in neutron/agent/linux/interface.py? See the in-line comment."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-01-06 17:10:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: (3 inline comments)

I personally do not feel it's a great idea to move this configuration parameter into interface.py. Details are in comments, but in a nutshell the ovs_vsctl timeout option would be registered in a module and used in another; also while use of neutron.agent.linux.interface implies use of ovs_lib the opposite is not true.

anyway, if you guys feel strongly about placing the options in another module I won't argue further."}, {'account_id': 1689, 'date': '2014-01-06 17:53:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)

I'm not insisting on changing this, but believe it is worth reconsidering.

The main modules for each agent (other than the L2 agents) generally are not specific to any particular L2 technology such as OVS. Instead, they are configured to use a driver class, typically (but not necessarily) in the neutron.agent.linux.interface module. Its these drivers that handle the specifics of plugging ports for openvswitch, linuxbridge, or whatever L2 technology is being used. That's why it seems to me that loading of the OVS-specific timeout config item fits better in neutron.agent.linux.interface than in the individual agents' L2-independent code."}, {'account_id': 7448, 'date': '2014-01-07 00:22:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

Looks like you have a few comments to address.  Adding an answer to a question that caused me to pause and think."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-01-08 23:02:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)

commit_message:
Make timeout for ovs-vsctl configurable

This patch adds a new configuration variable for the timeout on
ovs-vsctl commands, and sets the default timeout to 10 seconds.
This is aimed at allowing users to tune the agents in order to avoid
timeout errors on their deployments.

Change-Id: I73ea0d0de49a4b4a118bc2d68ad9c093ea122717
Closes-Bug: #1254520

commit_message:
first pass at adding havana repo for centOS/RHEL

Currently, the cookbooks attempt to install centOS/RHEL packages from
epel, since no other repo is configured.  epel contains folsom packages.

This commit drops in the official havana repo/gpg key so at least the
correct set of packages will attempt to be installed by chef.

Implements: blueprint centos-rhel-for-common

Change-Id: I76edc6538a71a8fb5f4242e8174aff9b3831834f

commit_message:
Cherry-pick the following commits from master:

* Made  improvements for rpmbuild
  I1dd7a54f7ade5414ad07cb8e12d0b018ecbc63c2
* Return status code instead of detailes
  Id0fe5dcae7ae19dee455a7ae8928e4a0d55fca26
* Add ability to delete file from service
  I6490ac2a391149a8660d5800b62ce8196e47bf00
* Add author field to the Compose Service form
  Increment service version after modification
  Forbid to edit version
  Closes bugs: #1262237, #1262239, #1262242
  I5061704c7a3ca96c26d79edfb9f551df3e2f80e2
* Update instance link formation due to changes in Havana
  Fixes-bug: #1262713
  I56e174f35ef4a60cffe31b0e619b53845a701ad6
* Add link with stack details in service details
  Ic3e34c9d341309ffd005a5479b2a6ef12b3bfe05
  Implements: blueprint add-stack-link
* Rename dynamic_ui package and normalize it.
  * Move muranodashboard.environments.services package to
    muranodashboard.dynamic_ui.
  * Move all code from dynamic_ui/__init__.py to dynamic_ui/services.py
    thus having normal empty __init__.py for dynamic_ui package (as in
      other packages).
  I395ee621578cb417314fe4960d74108deb848023
* Minor refactoring of dynamic_ui package.
  Remove one inner import in dynamic_ui.services and rewrite a bit
  iterate_over_services() function.
  If14022435a5ef269a448d5f568fe0f33421c9f23
* Do not log exception, if it is Http302 (redirect).
  I3488fc8523ec2e4628a26006c0211d2d468f189a
* Show more sensible error messages during Service Creation.
  If Metadata Repository is not available, show more concise error
  messages.
  Also refactor wrapper for handling Metadata Repository exceptions,
  thus allowing to throw-away some boilerplate code.
  I6acd94bf2ca397941f45bc4c8d9e9fe74678b5ee
  Closes-bug: #1263463

Change-Id: Ia814eccf6841f7dcc153cf0c3c7c793f0f358023

commit_message:
Add Manila API for policies and network info

Add server-side implemetation for 'policy' API.
Using network/policy_api module we're able to manage
information about policies.

Add server side for 'network-info' API.
Using network plug-in API we're able to manage specific
network information.

Partially implements bp: join-tenant-network

Change-Id: I36a404f9305bd3a58bc6c717bfac700ad25735f3

commit_message:
Add support for specifying tenant/user/token in the NoAuthMiddleware

This adds two new headers:

- X-Auth-User-ID - The User ID to use
- X-Auth-Project-ID - The Tenant/Project ID to use

Change-Id: I1b896f76732c8dcf527d05fa322926cc2b04c112

JSONEncoder. Up until today, we this was "not a problem", as
python-keystoneclient depended on simplejson, which provided the

commit_message:
Ensure Flask uses our JSON Encoder

Since the upgrade to Flask 0.10, we've not been using the correct
JSONEncoder. Up until today, we this was "not a problem", as
python-keystoneclient depended on simplejson, which provided the
necessary features.

python-keystoneclient 0.4.2 was released today, causing the issue
to finally surface.

Change-Id: Idc0e8f03608c80e097db2ea48b30f2bc0b8dbe5d
Closes-Bug: 1268607

commit_message:
Ensure that the diagnostics are user friendly

In the case when the value is a dictionary or array or longer than
the line then the diagnostics output will automatically wrap around
to ensure that the output is user friendly.

Part of the blueprint v3-diagnostics

Change-Id: Ia158fd99aeb0e6296fb232e881d0f01a13407dfc
Closes-bug: #1266402

commit_message:
clean up ubuntu versions

oneiric is long dead, remove references to it whenever possible
(one more subtle issue in cinder should be a seperate patch). This
includes removing the oneiric only tool build_uec.sh.

also remove the bulk of references to quantal, which is 8 months
out of support. note: raring only has support for the rest of the
month.

Change-Id: Ib17502be7572af76dc95560615221b48b970a547

this patch introduces the new naming scheme for Neutron VMware NSX
plugin configuration.

Related-blueprint: nvp-third-part-support (aka bp vmware-nsx-third-party)

commit_message:
Configuration changes required to support VMware NSX plugin

(Formerly known as Nicira NVP plugin).

Following Neutron change 79fbeb7ebebc0dfbe143aee96fbc250d1b9e7582,
this patch introduces the new naming scheme for Neutron VMware NSX
plugin configuration.

Related-blueprint: nvp-third-part-support (aka bp vmware-nsx-third-party)
Partial-implements blueprint: nicira-plugin-renaming

Change-Id: If7790887661507bfdec6d2b97c0f99609039aa73

commit_message:
Robustify service shutdown

* Save PID when using screen in screen_it()
* Add screen_stop()
* Call out service stop_*() in unstack.sh functions so screen_stop()
  can do its thing

Closes-bug: 1183449
Change-Id: Iac84231cfda960c4197de5b6e8ba6eb19225169a

commit_message:
Correct Qpid package name in files/apts/neutron

Ubuntu qpid server package is named as "qpidd", but
files/apts/neutron has an entry "qpid".

Closes-Bug: #1267459

commit_message:
Remove erroneous '--' from neutron net-create

As reported by George Shuklin, the neutron net-create command in the
OVS install instructions had an erroneous double-hyphen. Presumably,
this was a copy/paste error and this patch removes it.

Change-Id: I30a1c8a5329afb90c48653e117daf38de9fdb0ea
Closes-Bug: 1267043

commit_message:
Rewrite dynamic_ui to store Services data per-session.

Thus set of Services (and cleaned_data for them) for each user/tenant
will be isolated supporting per-tenant isolation blueprint.

Note that SESSION_ENGINE =
'django.contrib.sessions.backends.signed_cookies' doesn't work well
with Services' data storage because it has default limitation of 4096
bytes.

Closes-bug: #1264289
Change-Id: I3d0b46463470912cf6d7a36fddd84292689775da

commit_message:
Move most of code for dynamic UI form creation into metaclass.

Previously, all form definition parsing, fields creation and form
instantion were done in ServiceConfigurationForm instance __init__
method, which was not good indeed. This was done partly due to a need
to rapidly develop and debug dynamic_ui, due to the opinion that using
properties and attribute mappings (both of them are stored inside the
instantiated form) prevents separating form layout creation from
instantiating this form.

After some thoughts a proper way to separate them was found:
* move code that parses UI definitions, creates fields and widgets for
  a ServiceConfigurationForm subclass into a metaclass (called
  DynamicFormMetaclass);
* split property object creation into 2 phases: create RawProperty
  object in metaclass, while finalizing it (creating actual property
  object) once the form is instantiated;
* completing all assignments and calls that need a form instance in
  ServiceConfigurationForm __init__ method.

Creating form's fields layout during form class definition allows to
speed things a bit up, because form class is redefined only when
metadata is invalidated, while inside Django forms are instantiated
much more often.

Implements: blueprint dynamic-ui-optimization
Change-Id: I9b2617527b410abb7c60df978f9c00f7cef491d3

[{'account_id': 5196, 'date': '2013-12-11 01:17:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(5 inline comments)

I really like this idea, it's a great start. I started to do normal review comments on it but then decided you should probably iterate on this idea before it's ready for those kind of comments. I left what I had but it's not complete. When you get it to work in the gate I think it'll be ready for a real in depth review.

The only major issue I see right now is some of the hard coded assumptions. So with dynamic testing it is still dependent on a set of input data to build the test set, for example the ssh_users dict in this case. I feel like anything like that should be exposed through config options instead of being hard coded. You can't assume that everyone is going to be using a set of ubuntu cloud images to build the test set from. Right now in the gate this would never find a ssh_user match because we only have cirros images in glance. So moving forward I think anything that makes an assumption about an environment should be exposed as a config option.

I'm excited about this though it gives us some environment flexibility for scenarios. I'll definitely keep an eye on this."}, {'account_id': 1921, 'date': '2013-12-11 16:38:25.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-12-11 18:51:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Doesn't seem to work

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-06 07:15:59.000000000', 'message': "Input scenario capability for tempest

WIP - Do not merge

Adding the ability to generate multiple tests from
a template one based on input scenarios.
The implementation is based on testscenarios (added
to requirements.txt), and the correct behaviour
could be verified using unittest or testr + subunit,
both serial and parallel runs.

The generation of the array / matrix of tests relies
on the load_test protocol. nosetests does not implement
the protocol by default.

Static scenarios can be added to any tests with very
little effort. This commit introduces a couple of
dynamic scenarios:
- all flavours matching a configurable regex
- all images matching a configurable regex

Dynamic scenarios are coded in test_utils, and provided
by InputScenarioUtils. The class includes in the doc
an example on how to use input scenarios.

Additional scenarios could be AZs, or credentials.

This commit includes also a demo test to exemplify
how to use input scenarios.

This change partially implements blueprint
input-scenarios-for-scenario, and it's for demo purposes.

Implements: blueprint input-scenarios-for-scenario
Change-Id: Ia86f48772ac02d67faa1c7d764cb9dc0938f6452

commit_message:
Input scenario capability for tempest

Adding the ability to generate multiple tests from
a template one based on input scenarios.
The implementation is based on testscenarios (added
to requirements.txt), and the correct behaviour
could be verified using unittest or testr + subunit,
both serial and parallel runs.

The generation of the array / matrix of tests relies
on the load_test protocol. nosetests does not implement
the protocol by default.

Static scenarios can be added to any tests with very
little effort. This commit introduces a couple of
dynamic scenarios:
- all flavours matching a configurable regex
- all images matching a configurable regex

Dynamic scenarios are coded in test_utils, and provided
by InputScenarioUtils. The class includes in the doc
an example on how to use input scenarios.

Additional scenarios could be AZs, or credentials.

This commit adapts existing test_server_basic_ops
to use input scenarios, and include server
ssh verification.

This change implements blueprint input-scenarios-for-scenario.
Implements: blueprint input-scenarios-for-scenario

Change-Id: Ia86f48772ac02d67faa1c7d764cb9dc0938f6452

commit_message:
Remove old versions of grub2 from the yum cache

Before downloading and caching the latest version of grub2, we need to
first remove all old versions. Otherwise, the find command that writes
the grub2 version to /tmp/grub/install to install during the finalise
phase could pick one of the older versions of grub2 in the cache. This
will cause the install during the finalise phase to fail since the older
version of grub2 will conflict with the newer installed version of
grub2-tools.

Change-Id: I5b43e359db3ba81ed6283dfb41c7e89629516d38

commit_message:
Switch to Oslo's config generator

This fixes the sample configuration to contain proper
config groups alongway.

Regenerate sample config with oslo's config generator.

DocImpact: Removes the deprecated memcached_server
option from DEFAULT (now in keystone_authtoken group)

Closes-Bug: #1206650
Closes-Bug: #1260322

Change-Id: I170715bfe6ec7dad9f7317e7bb56cbb68034c4ec

commit_message:
Fix configurations reference for SPICE

The following options appear:
enabled = False	      (BoolOpt) enable spice related features
enabled = False	      (BoolOpt) Whether the V3 API is enabled or not

The option about V3 API is for nova v3 api, a mistake was also
fixed on nova.flagmappings.

Change-Id: I110f860dd220da4dcdf573b42f67abaee1945c22
Closes-bug: #1266977

How I see the problem:
1. there are two engines: old and heat
2. there are external calls to "instances" module, some of external calls are engine specific (e.g. "create_cluster"), some are not (e.g. "get_instances")
3. there are internal utility methods needed by both engines (e.g. "configure_instances")

What I want to see:
1. common internal utility methods hidden for outside
2. engines pushed to services that require then
3. easy way to access utility methods (like "get_instances") from outside. 

As I see this patch introduces "instances_common" that supposed to be item 1. Item 3 is already implemented.
But I don't see item 1 at all.

Before, it was possible to write "instances.get_instances". Now I don't see a way to do it right now because 
  a) I need to get engine instance somewhere (where?)
  b) utility method should be in engine interface and implemented in all engines. E.g. "check_cluster_exists" is not added to interface, but it is needed outside.

Suggestion: 
1. divide common methods on "public" and "private"
2. put private methods into "instances_common" (like in this path)
3. put all public utility methods into the place accessible from outside (utils/general or new file)
4. exclude utility methods from engine interface'}, {'account_id': 8411, 'date': '2013-12-18 21:10:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

What I want to see: 

1. common internal utility methods hidden for outside 

2. engines pushed to services that require then 

3. easy way to access utility methods (like "get_instances") from outside.

As I see this patch introduces "instances_common" that supposed to be item 1. Item 2 is already implemented. But I don't see item 3 at all.

commit_message:
Fix incorrect config of notification_driver

The 'Install the Compute agent for the Telemetry service' section
uses a wrong config of notification_drive, which is set to
non-existent ceilometer.compute.nova_driver instead of the right one:
ceilometer.compute.nova_notifier.

NOTE: This patch also fixes several content overflow problem.

Change-Id: Iacb5ae6d80f29e02fc210b07bdbca7dc92ee222e
Closes-Bug: #1268503

prevents instances on an internal network from establishing TCP
connections with a floating IP associate with an internal port
on the same Neutron network.

This patch add a SNAT rule to ensure connections coming from the
internal network always appear to the port associate with the

commit_message:
NVP plugin:fix connectivity to fip from internal nw

The current set of NAT rules configured in the NVP logical router
prevents instances on an internal network from establishing TCP
connections with a floating IP associate with an internal port
on the same Neutron network.

This patch add a SNAT rule to ensure connections coming from the
internal network always appear to the port associate with the
floating IP as coming from the external network.

Change-Id: I12da12ee136c61fddb04f2b216382b51d751a02c
Closes-Bug: 1221419
(cherry picked from commit ed2e32b03123ae8e7555b997152c1d8d941494f2)

commit_message:
Python3: use six's type when using isinstance

six.string_types replaces basestring() in Python 2 and str
in Python 3.

commit_message:
Passing stack_id argument to get_data view

Ignoring kwargs causes wrong key generation for
cache (for memoization) and hence, causes repeated call
of function with wrong arguments list.

Change-Id: I85391f30fa81a27496b3399108b4859b2234591e
Closes-Bug: #1268349

commit_message:
Removes BuiltInstanceTasks.get_volume_mountpoint

Reasons:
- Method is not being used in the project.
- Method has an unassigned variable used volume_id.

Changes:
- Removes get_volume_mountpoint from trove.taskmanager.models.

Change-Id: I2942a4cc952a473dd1ed1d52c8cb2205566b68ae
Closes-Bug: #1263371

commit_message:
Generate provider templates with Boolean params correctly

There is no Boolean parameter type, so properties of that type should be
converted to String parameters when generating a provider template from a
resource.

Change-Id: I779c17694da9dd1c0c0d3cc7deff924911d72bd4

commit_message:
Correct use of Fn::Split in generated provider templates

The argument to Fn::Split is a list containing the delimiter to split on
and the string to split. The former was omitted when using it in generated
templates.

This is good news, because it looks like nobody is using this feature.
CommaDelimtedLists don't really cut it for list parameters anyway, since
each list item may be e.g. a Map, so in the medium term we should convert
these over to using the Json parameter type in some way.

Change-Id: I02e0833d7032baa092bca97bd015659da07a9bae

commit_message:
Enabled F403 flake8 rule

Reasons:
- F403 is disabled.
- code contains "import *" statements.

Changes:
- Updates tox.ini to enable F403 rules.
- Updates code for F403 violation.

Change-Id: If932a910c073ae7bffb74908495f35dbc4f4d1f9
Closes-Bug: #1264724

commit_message:
VMware NSX: Fix db integrity error on dhcp port operations

If the dhcp port and network disappear, ensure that
the integrity constraint violation that results from
inserting the neutron/nsx port mapping to the DB does
not propagate the exception all the way through, but
instead is caught and handled correctly.

Closes-bug: #1265472

Change-Id: I3ae072729d579def0bd9658241eda1011a3dcfa0

commit_message:
Initial rubocop support for ChefSpec tests.

Per the mailing list thread, introducing Rubocop as a replacement for Tailor.
Assuming Jenkins likes this, more pedantic patches will follow to make Rubocop
happy. So far this is just spacing issues and adding UTF-8 headers, but more
work will need to be done to remove all of the changes for the .rubocop-todo.yml

Addresses: blueprint rubocop-for-block-storage
Change-Id: Ibb11739e452016c101995a371d031faeeb7e7683

commit_message:
Python3: use six's type when using isinstance

six.string_types replaces basestring() in Python 2 and str
in Python 3.

Change-Id: I7be12050f18c7fee659af5bb32044e2faff69172

commit_message:
Log service_status.status instead of service_status

Reasons:
- While printing the service status to log instead of printing status
  it prints the object id for service_status object.

Changes:
- Replaces service_status by service_status.status.
- Now it prints the service status to the log.

Change-Id: I98b78eb065bb6a2bce31a9dfcc591423e653dbae
Closes-Bug: #1265141

commit_message:
Adds missing dependency to the documentation

Trove depends on MySQL-python package, to compile and install it is
required libmysqlclient-dev, otherwise the installation procedure
described in 'doc/source/dev/manual_install.rst' will fail in recently
installed boxes.

Closes-Bug: #1261525
Change-Id: I0cc325eb7efb056efe9682fa3478795ae025bfa1

commit_message:
Tighten flake8 checks in Gating

There are a few checks that already pass:
 - F401 - unused imports of modules
 - F403 - from module import * used; unable to detect undefined names

And there are two (H401 and H403) that can be made
passing easily. Enable gating on all of them.

Change-Id: I9d3c49ecea1b2171d194ab6cc751316c252081e8

commit_message:
Make node deletion more stable

1. Use direct I/O for MBR erasing
2. Create pre-erase hook to avoid using
   of corrupted fs binaries
3. Use sysrq trigger to force node
   reset thus avoiding hanging reboot

Change-Id: Iafad920d9f2021bea374f58f828e5d33b820959d
Closes-bug: #1262524

Vincent, can you tell me where the quota itself would get corrected once the volume size is changed? The quota is committed before the RPC call as far as I can tell. Resize quota updates have specifically happened on the manager layer.'}, {'account_id': 2861, 'date': '2013-12-31 13:31:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 25:

Mike, there is a method in cinder/volume/flows/create_volume/__init__.py named "def get_api_flow(scheduler_rpcapi, volume_rpcapi, db,image_service, az_check_functor, create_what)", which is called by def create(...) Line 133 in cinder/volume/api.py.

QuotaReserveTask is responsible for reserving the quota and QuotaCommitTask commits the quota.

The size for the quota is from "raw_size", extracted by ExtractVolumeRequestTask and "raw_size" is the size input from the user(Please check "create_what" in the method def create(...)).

If we copy an image of 1G into a volume of 2G, the quota can reserve and commit this 2G, because this value comes from the user input. In this issue, the quota reservation and commit have the correct value, but the backend VMDK datastore allocates 1G instead of 2G, because the datastore reads the size of the image, not the user input size. It is the backend that makes the mistake. commit_message:
VMware: Take the volume size from the user input

When we create a volume from an image or a snapshot, we need to
take the size of the volume from the user input and validate whether
the size is appropriate instead of taking the image size as the
volume size directly.

Change-Id: I0b492ed41fdff57f9ab66de3da7876578fe2bd30
Closes-Bug: #1237557

commit_message:
Hide flag contents for "connection" and "postgresql"

PostgreSQL connection strings may contain passwords too, which we don't
want to log.

Fixes bug 1266804.

Change-Id: I4c2128cd4248172268b002a5d410eec729fd3eca

commit_message:
Increase padding to allow for smaller images

With smaller base images, such as Debian, the padding value used to
size the root filesystem does not leave enough room for grub which is
installed after the filesystem is created.

Change-Id: Ic2ab9e2efc9bf1b02f802ee47a36e3fff9c3512e

commit_message:
Enable horizon support on debian-based platforms

The default horizon element assumes apache is installed in /etc/httpd.
Add symlinks from /etc/apache2 to /etc/httpd structures to enable
horizon in these debian-based platforms.

Change-Id: I152aabf24bdb34fc82f32e928adbed7aaea3d735

commit_message:
replace type calls with isinstance

In store/__init__.py, there are two uses of the "type" method to
check type compatibility. It is better to use the "isinstance" method
since it will work for subtypes as well.

Change-Id: I20958aa449822cac2cb03e12557fded3f45a9e05
Closes-Bug: #1267074

commit_message:
Add -U to pip install command in tox.ini

Ask pip to upgrade packages in the virtualenv so that a long-lived
virtualenv is still kept up to date as external dependencies change.

Change-Id: Ifed85479166cb14273447467dfe8df6ba12df955

commit_message:
enable both extension level and action level policy check in v3 api

This enabels both extension level and action level policy check.
Then authorize must firstly pass extension level policy check, and
then pass the action level policy check. It will be convenient to
increase the access permissions for all actions in one extension,
when there are too many actions in that extension.

Partially implements bp v3-api-policy
DocImpact
Change-Id: Ie7211ef9ae7d1e8037b36ffc02a5b768850786cb

commit_message:
High level ssh library

This library is high-level wrapper around paramiko. It provides
easy to use interface for executing commands, getting output,
sending input etc.

Implements: blueprint common-ssh-client

commit_message:
Add bash completion support

Allow for tab-complete to work under bash. This is based on the same
implementation found in python-novaclient. This change allows for completion of
subcommands (image-list, image-show) as well as for completion of image IDs
and names for image-show. The image IDs and names are saved to a cache after
image-list is  called. Since the cache objects use the same format as
novaclient uses for completion, the same location is used: ~/.novaclient
This allow for  nova list commands to populate the cache for glance show
commands, and vice-versa.

Change-Id: Iee96077a2ca8a1f3a6f3cdd39527cb6f1899b145

commit_message:
Sync and cap requirements from all projects

* global-requirements.txt: Rebuild the list by installing
run-time and test requirements, including all transitive
dependencies, and cap them less than or equal to the latest package
versions unless they're for libraries we control.

Closes-Bug: 1172418
Change-Id: I5b921bb76128ac355651dcf78ad7d2bc846cc476

[{'created': '2013-12-27 03:07:49.000000000', 'message': "Fix ObjectClient* to have valid headers

Now, some ObjectClient* method don't send 'Content-Type' and 'Accept'
headers. This causes the response body is returned as a text/plain
format. In the normal test cases, we should set the 'Content-Type' and
'Accept' headers.

commit_message:
Fix ObjectClient* to have valid headers

Now, some ObjectClient* method don't send 'Content-Type' and 'Accept'
headers. This causes the response body is returned as a text/plain
format. In the normal test cases, we should set the 'Content-Type' and
'Accept' headers.

Change-Id: Ifbc34f3960bb2502e327c766987b4df943bb8545

commit_message:
VXLAN support

This patch is implementing support for VXLAN tunnel
type for OVS plugin.

Refactored neutron::plugins::ml2::validate_* to functions
so they can be used in other manifests in module.

Change-Id: Ic51ed794b27069809a151dc365ca108c8300c277
(cherry picked from commit 766561df83ea414ccf82423414863f30c6ce0761)

[{'created': '2014-01-09 04:08:47.000000000', 'message': 'Sync the kombu and amqp versions.

These versions were out of sync (kombu required a later amqp version),
which broke fresh installs such as via the Vagrantfile. This CR syncs
the versions.

Change-Id: Ie2cd9c50781bf014625b681e52e5506fd4904841
'}]
commit_message:
Sync the kombu and amqp versions.

These versions were out of sync (kombu required a later amqp version),
which broke fresh installs such as via the Vagrantfile. This CR syncs
the versions.

Change-Id: Ie2cd9c50781bf014625b681e52e5506fd4904841

commit_message:
Add API schema for v3 flavor_access API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

Change-Id: Ia3b4fa951c2f3867685ea6a619a39ac47dc4c3e6

commit_message:
Decouple the config dependence on glance domain

Move the configurations which core domain objects depend on to
common/config.py, and add a argument "task_time_to_live" of Task's
 __init__ method and TaskFactory's new_task method for delivering
the CONF.task.task_time_to_live value.
For convenience,the argument "task_time_to_live" is set a default value 48.

Change-Id: Iffda1ecd25470824c812d66a27fa64ebbaabcf07
Closes-Bug: #1250633

commit_message:
Adding invalid_property attr to support test code

Moving all base class calls to first line

Adding invalid_property to InvalidObject exception and
invalid_field to UnsupportedField exception.
Modified test code to check these attributes instead of
checking the exception message string.

Also updating NewOrderValidator and VerificationValidator
per bug #1246871

Change-Id: I0776d4a33652ec28c713037c2ef49e35c9b39e54
Implements: blueprint validation-improve-err-msgs

Added v3 interfaces in reference doc

commit_message:
Enable pep8 check for config.py in doc

Directory doc is excluded from pep8 check in tox.ini, since we
modified file doc/source/config.py, we should enable the check.

Change-Id: I057f1e6cb1c5f9a6a07043056078e4475f66f288

commit_message:
Add API schema for v3 extended_volumes API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

Change-Id: If0ebee7a8661baae9eea1e7ce586695b9e575afc

commit_message:
Make sure instance_type_id index exist when db sync

When upgrade database from folsom to grizzly, then to havana. 184 -> 185 will
raise a exception. The reason is table 'instance_type_projects' lost a index
'instance_type_id' after running 174_add_instance_type_access_uc.

The patch make sure the index 'instance_type_id' is existed after adding UC.

Change-Id: Ib15dc87aa8af3f0f8070693283da77ee66fd42c8
Closes-Bug: #1239484

commit_message:
Fix inappropriate logouts on load-balanced Horizon

The session timeout code in the horizon/middleware.py can cause
inappropriate timeouts/logouts when running Horizon behind a load
balancer on two machines that are slightly out of sync time-wise.

Use timestamps rather than datetime as the arithmetic is simpler.

Closes-bug: #1243277
(cherry-picked from commit 13355dacdbfa9ef14a4e1c16afeffaece5c13a39,
 minus the unrelated settings.py changes.)

Change-Id: If218d100d25c544b37a2517bd260838092a5f8cf

commit_message:
Removes use of timeutils.set_time_override

The set_time_override function in timeutils was written as a
helper function to mock utcnow for unittests before 'mock' was
generally used. Now that we have mock and fixture, we no longer
need to use it.

Change-Id: I9a0727edab12ccd5f1e4eb4f5f62d588f5a0faee
Partial-Bug: #1266962

commit_message:
Fix broken i18n support

In notification and publisher.rpc module, there are some log messages
don't support i18n, this patch fixes them.

NOTE: rename unused variable from _ to n, because it will overshadow
global _ of gettext.

Change-Id: Ic703fe6536234f4d51a84f4a3b2e04049ec6f3b5
Closes-Bug: #1263711

commit_message:
Removes unnecessary api-paste.ini configuration

Paremeter api_paste_config defaults to '/etc/nova/api-paste.ini',
so it is not needed to set it in nova.conf. Without having
the parameter in nova.conf we can use this module together
with dist.conf. Also filter:authtoken parameters should be
in nova.conf and not in api-paste.ini. Removes filter:authtoken
configuration from api-paste.ini in case it is filled there.

Change-Id: I4798124b3c75c012653c9868c771146f23cf4cc7
(cherry picked from commit ee469886921b7168a0ae974f7557d355af98aacb)

commit_message:
Add support for allow_pagination and allow_sorting

Neutron has boolean parameters for enabling/disabling pagination and
sorting on the server side. This patch adds the ability to configure
these parameters via the neutron class.

Change-Id: Ibf105b828e1ca504f8f6b5292b8ad0335c658d6d

commit_message:
Fix i18n problem in processutils module

Some texts in processutils module use raw string instead of gettext,
they should be fixed since this module already supports i18n.

Change-Id: I6868301f076d4b9b6e604238bacce6207bbce2ab
Closes-Bug: #1215006

commit_message:
auth_token tests use assertIs/Not/None

The tests in test_auth_token_middleware were using
assertEqual(res, None) and assertNotEqual(res, None) when they
should use assertIsNone and assertIsNotNone.

Change-Id: Ib1601b3a6101f843d9c29f3cd00aab339e671e61

commit_message:
Add coverage option to run_tests.sh

This commit adds a new option to run_tests.sh to run the unit tests
with coverage enabled. If the coverage arg is specified a coverage
report will be generated after the unit tests are run.

Change-Id: I1473fe4da96aecd0b3b0bf3a3ec1e3e87039271b

commit_message:
Skip simple_tenant_usage related tests

This patch adds skip decorator for simple_tenant_usage related tests.
After use 'project' instead of 'tenant' in simple_tenant_usage v3,
will update those tests.

Related patches:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/58443/
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/58444/

Change-Id: Ifcb30d1eade2b7a7196c3c0a6b4165e5fdce2944
Related-Bug: #1265416

commit_message:
Adds quota usage support for the V3 API

Adds the ability to do a detailed query from the
os-quota-sets V3 API extension. This was an interface
added in V3 to allow for the querying of current quota
usage. Adds a shell command quota-usage which
uses this interface to show current quota usage as well
as the limit.

The absolute limits response was removed from
the limits extension in a9e29b7e9fbe14ab42f24802a6d2a457a6317ba3
and so the corresponding novaclient command is also removed.
The "quota-show-usage" command now shows the same information.

Differences between the V2 and V3 API are described here:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3

Partially implements blueprint v3-api

Change-Id: I5db72d42120f4ad7a86fbfce20382988f6bbf5d3

commit_message:
Remove Swift container-sync test skipping

The skipping reason was bug #1093743 that
is currently marked as invalid in Swift bugtracker.

This patch remove the skip and propose some
refactoring to the test code.

The test is marked as slow as it can take long
to run as it depends on container-sync process run
internal which is 300 seconds by default.

Change-Id: I939a014646b42cb2a461f874a5ad0edfc79c5561

Unfortunately this is the same problem I ran into when I tried to sync this change to Neutron, and I was never able to resolve it myself.

commit_message:
Update lockutils and fixture in openstack.common

lockutils: included commits:
  8b2b0b7 Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._
  6d0a6c3 Correct invalid docstrings
  12bcdb7 Remove vim header
  79e6bc6 fix lockutils.lock() to make it thread-safe
  ace5120 Add main() to lockutils that creates temp dir for locks
  537d8e2 Allow lockutils to get lock_path conf from envvar
  371fa42 Move LockFixture into a fixtures module
  d498c42 Fix to properly log when we release a semaphore
  29d387c Add LockFixture to lockutils
  3e3ac0c Modify lockutils.py due to dispose of eventlet
  90b6a65 Fix locking bug
  27d4b41 Move synchronized body to a first-class function
  15c17fb Make lock_file_prefix optional
  1a2df89 Enable H302 hacking check

fixture: created, included commits:
  45658e2 Fix violations of H302:import only modules
  12bcdb7 Remove vim header
  3970d46 Fix typos in oslo
  371fa42 Move LockFixture into a fixtures module
  f4a4855 Consolidate the use of stubs
  6111131 Make openstack.common.fixture.config Py3 compliant
  3906979 Add a fixture for dealing with config
  d332cca Add a fixture for dealing with mock patching.
  1bc3ecf Start adding reusable test fixtures.

Also tox.ini was corrected to let lockutils work in tests.

This change is needed for work on bp: db-sync-models-with-migrations

Closes-Bug: #1065531

Change-Id: I139f30b4767ff2c9d1f01ee728823859c09b3859

commit_message:
Fix mistake in usage drop_constraint parameters

In migration e197124d4b9_add_unique_constrain mistake in usage
drop_constraint parameter type_ and positional arguments name
and table_name.

The same mistake was already fixed in migration
63afba73813_ovs_tunnelendpoints_id_unique.

Change-Id: I6a250e55ea53048bb11afd71fecf94da6f0c7421
Closes-bug: #1257607

commit_message:
Removes use of timeutils.set_time_override

The set_time_override function in timeutils was written as a
helper function to mock utcnow for unittests before 'mock' was
generally used. Now that we have mock and fixture, we no longer
need to use it.

Partial-Bug: #1266962

Change-Id: I56935911a08ccd9847419eb118af2d2c9dd6c1cd

[{'created': '2014-01-03 10:44:18.000000000', 'message': 'Fix duplicate topic messages for Qpid topology=2

Manually applied ef406a21782134aeefb944f74b3f1a47d6169318 from
oslo-incubator to get the fix required for bug 1257293.

Copying the original commit message from oslo-incubator below.

"""
When multiple RPC servers (consumers) are subscribed to the same RPC
topic, a single RPC request to that topic should be received by only
one of the consumers.  A bug in the QPID driver caused every consumer
to receive a copy of the RPC request.  This bug affects only Topology
version 2.  This patch will cause a single queue to be created for
each topic, and shared among all consumers of that topic.  This
results in each RPC request being received by only one consumer,
in turn across all the competing consumers.
"""

Change-Id: I76bfa5b48bad4a70fbf06b74f4cc8234af6610c2
Closes-bug: #1257293.
'}]
commit_message:
Fix duplicate topic messages for Qpid topology=2

Manually applied ef406a21782134aeefb944f74b3f1a47d6169318 from
oslo-incubator to get the fix required for bug 1257293.

Copying the original commit message from oslo-incubator below.

"""
When multiple RPC servers (consumers) are subscribed to the same RPC
topic, a single RPC request to that topic should be received by only
one of the consumers.  A bug in the QPID driver caused every consumer
to receive a copy of the RPC request.  This bug affects only Topology
version 2.  This patch will cause a single queue to be created for
each topic, and shared among all consumers of that topic.  This
results in each RPC request being received by only one consumer,
in turn across all the competing consumers.
"""

Change-Id: I76bfa5b48bad4a70fbf06b74f4cc8234af6610c2
Closes-bug: #1257293.

commit_message:
Don't need session.flush in context managed by session

Within the scope of a single method, keeping all the reads and writes within
the context managed by a single session. In this way, the session's __exit__
handler will take care of calling flush() and commit() for you.
If using this approach, you should not explicitly call flush() or commit().
See http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/rel_0_7/orm/session.html#committing

Closes-Bug: #1258044
Change-Id: I1125c72712203f1594ef245761dbfc25ed31eab2

commit_message:
Print driver exception on retype

If the driver raises an exception, make sure it is printed. Also change
the logging level from info to error because an exception should not be
thrown under normal conditions.

Change-Id: I003959c3f7c7667124ef61911587012fd4e1d667
Closes-Bug: #1268294

commit_message:
Fix race condition on ml2 delete and update port methods

Synchronize access to ports table when deleting and updating
a port. Otherwise concurrent update/delete request for the same port
may cause neutron server to throw an exception and return
'500 Internal server error' for such requests.

Change-Id: I868002643147ce6baace5671cffb38b4f5e66729
Closes-Bug: #1266537

commit_message:
Sync oslo-incubator rpc	module

Sync oslo-incubator rpc module with oslo-incubator commit
f8f6fd46b3b9264c21c0ee5547a4e8236cb257ac

Updates consist in using six.iteritem and fixing some typos.

Remove securemessage.py, which in not used anywhere, and dropped from
oslo-incubator since commit f88d59ab8a456e7d2d5a22fc5591491d2f85bdf4

$ python update.py --nodeps --base keystone --dest-dir ../keystone/ --modules rpc
$ git rm keystone/openstack/common/rpc/securemessage.py

Change-Id: I890cf1ce89ce5946522f7891be71a3e58ecc1af3

commit_message:
Cleanup the flake8 section of tox.ini

* Stop ignoring F403 as we have no cases of it anyway
* Cleanup the comments to make it clear what is ignored on purpose and
  what is ignored until we clean up the code.

Change-Id: I2500e2db70b9c71fbed781d8f7b7c80eee45140f

orchestration: Add API docs for stack actions

suspend and resume, added to the API during the Havana cycle.

commit_message:
Clarified example architectures

I clarified the example architectures section to cover the two primary
architectures assumed throughout the installation guide. This patch
fixes the immediate issue of operators not understanding assumptions
made by the guide. A future patch for this bug will include improved
text and diagrams based on example architectures chosen for Icehouse.

Change-Id: I2529f7a4a66c0e7442d675f65909579aba3a0ad6
backport: havana
Partial-Bug: #1263719

commit_message:
Update account quota doc

A note was added stating that the same limitations apply to
account quotas as for container quotas. An example on uploads
without a content-length headers was added.

Related-Bug: 1267659

commit_message:
Synchronized with oslo db and db.sqlalchemy

In most cases Oslo-incubator contains the most relevant code.
Furthermore in certain cases exists bugs which can be fixed by
synchronization with Oslo. Thus regular sync is required.

                        Changes from oslo-incubator
==============================================================================
8b2b0b7 Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._
9bc593e Add docstring for exception handlers of session
855644a Removal of _REPOSITORY global variable.
ea6caf9 Remove string.lowercase usage
a33989e Remove eventlet tpool from common db.api
e40903b Database hook enabling traditional mode at MySQL
f2115a0 Replace xrange in for loop with range
c802fa6 SQLAlchemy error patterns improved
1c1f199 Remove unused import
6d0a6c3 Correct invalid docstrings
fb0e86a Use six.moves.configparser instead of ConfigParser
6603e8f Remove sqlalchemy-migrate 0.7.3 patching
97d8cf4 Remove lazy loading of database backend
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Synced from Oslo-Incubator commit: 517c4cc65969f93b4b758a568725a1625abfd24d

Change-Id: Ida6b38b8e41c73c67170e4ec43943e661f014629

commit_message:
Skip unconfigurable drivers for store initialization

All enabled/known store drivers are currently initialized and configured
by Glance when API daemon startup, and the driver(s) which could not be
configured correctly fail are not skipped. This patch explicitly skips
the stores with bad configuration and logs the same.

Change-Id: Ie14b1fb2f554e12cf82512f1d84390619d35a886
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

commit_message:
Cleanup test_associate_project_endpoint_extension

This moves the addCleanup closer to where it's required and
takes care of a TODO. Turns out that cleanup up self.conf_files
is required.

Change-Id: I4229b950fe3dc7e575f921f2b63c4462ed459108

commit_message:
adding policy checks for cinder

Adding cinder policy rules file for policy checks. Implementing
rule checks as well. Some cinder API calls actually hit nova, so
adding those calls as well.

Also a couple of improvements to the Horizon policy engine. First,
now providing the token scope project_id and user_id as targets by
default, unless otherwise specified.  Most service policy rules
check on or both of these.  Second, checking to see if rule exists,
before attempting enforcement.  If the rule does not exist, using
the default rule for that service.  This now matches what the
service policy engines do.

Implements: blueprint block-rbac

Change-Id: Ifef08b8975280f4e621ba8eebec9d405e1e870a2

commit_message:
Add API schema for v3 agents API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

Change-Id: Iae1bff0e853e1dc597ebdca07efeb477b105469e

commit_message:
Define common API parameter types

This patch defines some common API parameter types for API validation.
By sharing the parameter types between the whole Nova API, that would
make the APIs more consistent.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

Change-Id: Ic1e25c8ccedbcefc5818f223049eaa3f9eb04959

commit_message:
Sync with oslo-incubator

Modules held back:

- openstack.common.policy. Bug #1268315.

Compatibility changes made:

- Additional arguments added to the Context object
- RPC Services no longer need to explicitly wait on
  the rpc consumer thread
- Our openstack-common.conf file explicitly includes
  transitive dependencies. This is no longer necessary.
  Bug #1268314.

Additional changes still necessary:

- We use some depreciated modules (WSGI), we need to remove
  our dependence on these. Bug #1268313.

Change-Id: Ia52b386a928e1d03709dfdb23f0d504c7d01bc19
Oslo-SHA1: 8710dbacfd7d8dad58fccbdd4ffda7246dcbbb7c

commit_message:
Update openstack/common/lockutils

The following commits are in this update:

79e6bc6 fix lockutils.lock() to make it thread-safe
ace5120 Add main() to lockutils that creates temp dir for locks
537d8e2 Allow lockutils to get lock_path conf from envvar

Change-Id: I2190d0aae72ef4a29daf8f7d960da82a33b331b4

Fix Brick LVM test command parsing

The case reporting only one fake-volumes VG was never hit, which also
caused us to not test the lvcreate -T path.

commit_message:
Python 3: use six.iteritems() instead of iteritems()

Six.iteritems() replaces dictionary.iteritems() on Python 2 and
dictionary.items() on Python 3.

Change-Id: I12fda5f20d2f4fe8227e45b2fe46b332f63deb97

commit_message:
Fix asserttion of types

Some code in tests is uisng assertTrue(isinstance(A, B))
or assertEqual(B, type(A)). assertIsInstance must be used instead.

assertIsInstance is provided by testtools package, so this change is not
breaking backward compatibility with Python 2.6.

Closes-Bug: #1259941

Change-Id: Ib601aebabc0ff0318cd87cc199c808e6b59f7c9f

commit_message:
Put cinder rootwrap config in separate function

Separate out Cinder's rootwrap configuration so that it can be called
from Grenade's upgrade scripts. This follows the same model as Nova uses
with configure_nova_rootwrap() which can be called from Grenade to
refresh rootwrap config.

Change-Id: Id808abc2b5754443362b3de4b3453e305d3720f3

commit_message:
Drop Chance/SimpleScheduler Implementation

This patch removes the implementation of ChanceScheduler and SimpleScheduler
as previous changes have made sure they are internally replaced by
FilterScheduler.

The "max_gigabytes" config option is deprecated and will leave it like that
for one more release before we can remove it.

DocImpact: "ChanceScheduler and SimpleScheduler have been deprecated and
their implementation have been removed from Cinder."

Implement bp: deprecate-chance-and-simple-schedulers

Change-Id: Ifb1cb25e3bb4cdf26fa3283336b83fce5c97141e

commit_message:
Print driver exception on retype

If the driver raises an exception, make sure it is printed. Also change
the logging level from info to error because an exception should not be
thrown under normal conditions.

Closes-Bug: #1268294

Change-Id: I6b492a25abd9606c3bd0669450df0773209177f1

A number of MySQL migration tests fail because the test case
is verifying that an sqlalchemy.types.BOOLEAN column was created.
When the column type is checked, however, mysql reports the type as
sqlalchemy.dialects.mysql.TINYINT.  The mismatch causes numerous
test cases to fail for MySQL.

commit_message:
Add bool_type dictionary to test_migrations

A number of MySQL migration tests fail because the test case
is verifying that an sqlalchemy.types.BOOLEAN column was created.
When the column type is checked, however, mysql reports the type as
sqlalchemy.dialects.mysql.TINYINT.  The mismatch causes numerous
test cases to fail for MySQL.

This creates a dictionary for each engine being tested to handle the
different boolean types.

postgresql and DB2 encounter similar issues.  Subsequent patches
will make the appropriate changes for those databases.

Change-Id: I81cb3c6feeacf887f1f473ec54414e0e215d2c24
Closes-bug: 1260126

commit_message:
Update README to the valid Oslo-incubator doc

Currently, the README in `openstack/common/` contains a link
to a blank page.
This patch changes the link to a valid documentation page.

Change-Id: I6c7a7a5fcef76f49b5d38c79b10a2a849046a32f
Closes-Bug: #1268051

commit_message:
Prevent min_disk and min_ram from being negative

At the moment, in both api versions, min_disk and min_ram can be set to
negative value - which doesn't make sense. This commit fixes this behavior
in the two versions of the glance api.

Change-Id: Ib7855c1d928ab8262dd2a109619a4e3d2299ff9e
Closes-bug: #1265711

commit_message:
Update cinderclient to skip the additional GET during create

With change https://review.openstack.org/64945 cinder V2 API now
returns volume details. Updated do_create in cinderclient
to remove additional GET call.

Change-Id: I2a36f2fa865b52f228bad44e0a9c67d49228321e
Partial-Bug: #1265893

commit_message:
Set image size to None after removing all locations

Based on current design, the image size should be updated to
None if there is no location assocaited with the image. This
patch fixes this issue and introduces some related changes.

Closes-Bug: #1263729

Change-Id: I893468f1dc320ea9434f07c3a32f978cd5941b33

commit_message:
Fix setup-clienttools to not use a subshell

Looping over a subshelled echo is a pointless use of a subshell, since
for loops do not require it.

Change-Id: I1fd00e4c66b485b310561f7809fec2c7921f0f5c

commit_message:
Remove unused message from iogrp_data setup

The iogrp_data is initialized during do_setup loaded.
The vdisk_count is originally used but later removed.
In ValueException raised, the variable is no longer required.
Remove this will give a clearer message when 
ValueException raised.

Change-Id: Ib7b6c6a870ddd7932e8da1436d615f9ee458bd93
Closes-Bug: #1266321

commit_message:
Fix v3 test_list_servers_negative

1) for alt_manager was used v2 servers client, instead v3,
as for common manager.
2) due to bug #1252971, it should be fixed as for v2 Test Suite.
See merged commit:
https://github.com/openstack/tempest/commit/892d43567bebc31283b56f9e22d554ee98b60e06

Change-Id: Ib3af06a46672f1e331f5c3bcd6e70cf006ec011b
Closes-Bug: #1266105

commit_message:
Use install_venv from oslo to fix no post_process issue

In a recent oslo sync commit Ieb73d5f799423fa8abf71634c86601ba6d32df2f
post_process() has been removed from tools/install_venv_common.py, which
is still called in tools/install_venv.py

Further investigation shows install_venv.py has some legacy distro
specific code, which should be removed at the time introducing
install_venv_common from oslo.

This change switch tools/install_venv.py to use oslo code to align the
effort as well as fixing original no 'post_process' issue.

Changes being pulled into in install_venv are:
12bcdb7 - 2013-11-25 12:16:11 +0800 - Remove vim header
b5cca99 - 2013-10-09 21:34:00 +0100 - Remove obsolete
redhat-eventlet.patch
9378d3c - 2013-08-13 18:06:11 +0300 - Move `./run_tests.sh` to Oslo

Note: openstack-common.conf is not updated, because the project name
variable in install_venv has to be modified after syncing from oslo.
That makes it not an exact sync but modification after sync. Besides
other openstack projects using install_venv from oslo also don't change
openstack-common.conf. So this patch simply follow the common practice
here.

Change-Id: I78a7563fbbde70cfd98cf1bd7a5a4eec5370d31d
Closes-Bug: #1263940

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary line in test_auth

TestCase sets up the kvs identity backend already, by using
test_overrides.conf, so this line doesn't do anything and is going
to lead to confusion if test_overrides.conf changes to a different
backend.

Change-Id: I3f62e70a0dd7a27b675a29a56bfbccffa1b9be50

commit_message:
Allow programmatic reloading of Swift hash path config

New util's function validate_hash_conf allows you to programmatically reload
swift.conf and hash path global vars HASH_PATH_SUFFIX and HASH_PATH_PREFIX
when they are invalid.

When you load swift.common.utils before you have a swift.conf there's no good
way to force a re-read of swift.conf and repopulate the hash path config
options - short of restarting the process or reloading the module - both of
which are hard to unittest.  This should be no worse in general and in some
cases easier.

Change-Id: I1ff22c5647f127f65589762b3026f82c9f9401c1

commit_message:
Add API schema for v3 keypairs API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

Change-Id: I484fc2807721b5bfe0f1a11c3811b99a13d920aa

commit_message:
Handle exceptions outside of session context

Sqlalchemy's database exceptions are raised when commit changes to
database, db model's update method will not trigger exception, need
handle exceptions outside of session context. This was also added
in docstring for db. See https://review.openstack.org/#/c/60144/

Change-Id: I5dbe3a0ae5504e72ad44b626233e904189d94f74

commit_message:
Add -U to pip install command in tox.ini

Ask pip to upgrade packages in the virtualenv so that a long-lived
virtualenv is still kept up to date as external dependencies change.

commit_message:
Return policy error, not generic error

When nova net-create and net-delete are prohibited by policy, we should
raise policy violation error (403) to the user instead of service
unavailable (503) error which is incorrect.

Closes-Bug: #1260905
Change-Id: I2edc0eb09f1dc192ba47184ed24fc49e4fcd4b79

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-01-07 07:51:58.000000000', 'message': "Fix tab-completion of --flags under OS X

--flags were not tab-completing under OS X. This was due to the whitespace
collapsing regular expression using the '+' token (meaning one-or-more), which
isn't supported in OS X's version of sed.

Using the more portable '  *' instead of '[  ]+' fixes this.

Additional cleanups

* Remove unecessary embedding of tabs in the file (nova bash-complete doesn't
  emit tabs, so the regular expressions don't have to handle them)

* Restore logic to exclude -h from tab-completion (was lost in last
  tab-completion cleanup)

* Add similar exclude logic for -i

Fixes bug 1266667

commit_message:
Fix tab-completion of --flags under OS X

--flags were not tab-completing under OS X. This was due to the whitespace
collapsing regular expression using the '+' token (meaning one-or-more), which
isn't supported in OS X's version of sed.

Using the more portable '  *' instead of '[  ]+' fixes this.

Additional cleanups

* Remove unecessary embedding of tabs in the file (nova bash-complete doesn't
  emit tabs, so the regular expressions don't have to handle them)

* Restore logic to exclude -h from tab-completion (was lost in last
  tab-completion cleanup)

* Add similar exclude logic for -i

Fixes bug 1266667

Change-Id: I7e1fe8382d9b5295d0bbc1cde2b89550d5a4e21c

commit_message:
Expose quota detail with os-quota-detail API extension

API V3 has already implemented a feature in commit 8b388f to expose
detailed quota infomation, i.e in_use, reserved, and limit.

Since it is a useful feature, and V2 api gonna be around for long
time, this change backported it to V2 api.

Due to API stability concern, implemented as a separate API extension,
hence could be enabled/disabled by deployer.

API examples:
GET v2/{tenant_id}/os-quota-sets/{tenant_id}/detail
GET v2/{tenant_id}/os-quota-sets/{tenant_id}/detail?user_id={user_id}

DocImpact

Closes-bug: #1183870
Implements blueprint expose-quota-details

Change-Id: Iaf4faedddab244a1a9ee4e221112ba58dfd782e9

commit_message:
when no config files can be used, raise ConfigFilesNotFoundError

when no config files can be used, this will raise ConfigFilesNotFoundError.
so the users can make sure they are using the config file not the
default value.

Closes-Bug #1265737

Change-Id: I16af57b4a2f1d477385b56846ca080801256c6d8

commit_message:
Add an option to enable tcp_keepalive for the wsgi server

This option is useful in situations where the wsgi
server runs behind a load balancer. Setting tcp_keepalive
to True will enable keepalive on the server socket.

Change-Id: Icd12a755b54fd2f6b3b5b7fb21f2338b90fc1314

'}, {'account_id': 1561, 'date': '2014-01-03 16:28:01.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

This is actually a bit controversial.

There is only one other place where we do this explicitly right now (and you can blame me if you don't like it).  It's in (add|remove)_fixed_ip_to_instance in nova/compute/manager.py.

updated_at is automatically updated any time the db record for the instance changes.  Ideally that's the end of it.  The tricky part is that we expose this value through the API.  From an API user perspective, I expect that this value  be updated any time I do anything to an instance.  I would include attaching/detaching volumes in that.

So, I'm in favor of this change because I think it results in what users would most likely expect."}, {'account_id': 5511, 'date': '2014-01-03 16:34:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

I don't like this approach, even though I see it happening all over the place.

However it does fix an actual bug so I am a bit divided.

updated_at will automatically be updated on every update, and we are moving to objects now, so with it would be cleaner to try to do this using objects in a general way (maybe a decorator that does this).

There are patches that convert these code paths to objects already up for review fwiw (see https://review.openstack.org/#/c/63827)
If you feel that this approach is not something you'd want to try to hack yourself - maybe we can accept this and fix it but imho it is suboptimal.

And I can't say that it is clear to me 100% that attaching a volume requires the updated_at to change."}, {'account_id': 4573, 'date': '2014-01-03 22:20:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Bump instance updated_at on volume change

Update attach_volume and detach_volume code paths to update the
updated_at field of the instance, since from the user's perspective
through the API, they have made a change to the instance's
configuration. In that case, it makes sense to expect that the
updated_at field gets changed.

Closes-Bug: #1250066

Change-Id: I6279025054d0f8c0c895575f24436d9aee4e9b63

commit_message:
Use auth_url as mgmt_url if not admin identity

If admin identity endpoint is not found from the returned service catalog,
the given message error is Unable to authorize user by shell.py, when
httpclient.py raises an AuthorizationFailure exception with the message
Current authorization does not have a known management url but this one
is suppressed by the message previously mentioned in shell.py, in order
to solve this bug it is possible to use the auth_url as management_url.

After last review I am going to keep the current approach with reviewers
(Dolph and ayoung) in other case we can change the approach to solve this
bug as Jamie Lennox has suggested, maybe it can be solved catching the
exception and showing a message indicating that mgt_url doesn't anymore
exist.

Change-Id: I5440b94b40acd1cd0f207913a21cfab22f7d4c87
Closes-Bug: #1208991

commit_message:
WIP: Add scheduler_hints to the output of "nova show"

Scheduler_hints now stored in table of instances and will also be
used by scheduler for live migration validation, so it is better
to add scheduler_hints to the output of "nova show" for better debug
ability.

Implements part of bp validate-targethost-live-migration

Change-Id: If64c78aa58b1e9bb10f0fa75f174486de6b87b00

commit_message:
Do not use contextlib.nested if only mock one function

There are some test cases in test_compute_mgr.py using contextlib.nested
to mock up functions even there is only one function needs to be mocked.

We should use mock.patch.object directly if only mock one function.

Change-Id: I30f05d0dcb442d426358b673f0e638ace8b85e0e
Closes-Bug: #1263602

commit_message:
Allow concurrency to be tweaked for tempest

This adds a knob for tweaking the tempest concurrency, but sets the
default to 4 (what we run at now by default).

This was borrowed from https://review.opensta+ck.org/#/c/58605/3

Change-Id: I90f7da9f6d72858abf58aff35aa2037de4b5e0af

[{'created': '2014-01-10 17:44:45.000000000', 'message': 'trusts API test, avoid creating duplicate user

We currently call create_trustor_and_roles twice, in the base
class and the test class, which is wrong and results in the test
leaving a user behind which is not cleaned up.  So only call it
in the test class, because we need self._interface to be set.

Change-Id: I9b96ae4435714d17bfd2b0b2abe570d98e61bfa6
Closes-Bug: #1267704
'}]
commit_message:
trusts API test, avoid creating duplicate user

We currently call create_trustor_and_roles twice, in the base
class and the test class, which is wrong and results in the test
leaving a user behind which is not cleaned up.  So only call it
in the test class, because we need self._interface to be set.

Change-Id: I9b96ae4435714d17bfd2b0b2abe570d98e61bfa6
Closes-Bug: #1267704

commit_message:
List Nova and Cinder extensions in debug log

For debugging purposes and post-processing Tempest logs it is useful
to get a list of Nova and Cinder extensions. This patch logs every
found extension to the debug log as a comma-separated list.

Change-Id: Ib550913e6c7b8b9eef12569c0ad7022c44b1f84d

commit_message:
Don't reset LOCAL_PATH if it's already set

If LOCAL_PATH is set in local_settings, then settings should
not override it, even if SECRET_KEY is unset.

Change-Id: I6aca03f65afddffb6cdd00e4084a8ab9b2255ef1
Closes-Bug: #1254694

commit_message:
Fixes handling of arrays in XML to JSON conversion

The xml to json method in compute/xml/common.py has
an option to specify which XML elements shall be translated
to a list rather than a dict.
The current implementation though applies only for the
first level of elements and it's not passed down to
children elements.

Closes-Bug: #1267867
Change-Id: I70f6b95fbeac2a9e28e935e506ba43d183690994

Remove the FWaaS Noop driver as the default and raise an exception
when the fwaas_driver.ini file has an enabled flag without any
associated driver. This communicates a misconfiguration clearly.
The Noop driver is moved to unit tests where it is used.

commit_message:
Remove FWaaS Noop driver as default and move to unit tests dir

Remove the FWaaS Noop driver as the default and raise an exception
when the fwaas_driver.ini file has an enabled flag without any
associated driver. This communicates a misconfiguration clearly.
The Noop driver is moved to unit tests where it is used.
Also some cleanups in related area.

Closes-Bug: #1250841

Change-Id: Ib6345923df05994ceffc0b1cbf265b53c23e97f1

commit_message:
Fix reference config before initialization in cli tests

In 'setUpClass' method config groups were referenced
before initialization using still empty oslo.config
which is empty if use without other cli test suites.
Fixed.

Change-Id: I4f0109617bf98bbb375cfcf816c074762b9fc69a
Closes-Bug: #1265909

commit_message:
Fix call to store.safe_delete_from_backend

When uploading data of a newly created image to a local filesystem
store, if the image data size exceeds the quota allocated to the user
then the operation fails with a "500 Internal Server Error".

This bug is triggered only when using chunked transfers to upload the
image data (curl and glanceclient both use chunked transfers).

When using chunked transfers the 'Content-Length' header is not set and
so the quota checking code in start of quota.ImageProxy.set_data() is
skipped. Furthermore, because of the missing size info, the store
downloads the entire image data without checking for the quota (the
quota is checked only after the image data has been downloaded and the
size determined).

If after the image data has been downloaded it is found that the quota
has been exceeded, then the StorageQuotaFull exception is raised and a
call to store.safe_delete_from_backend() made to clean up the image
data. But the 'location' and 'context' parameters to this call are given
in the wrong order and so this operation raises an (uncaught) exception,
giving rise to this bug.

This bug was not caught by existing tests because existing quota tests
don't use chunked transfer.

This commit fixes the order of the parameters and adds quota tests using
chunked transfers.

Change-Id: Ib8ab11f2115e3aead98af70788eaa45c2c33219c

commit_message:
Avoid unnecessary use of rootwrap for some network commands

Every time we run something as root with rootwrap, it takes about
ten times longer (setup-wise anyway). For things that don't need
to be run as root, we should avoid this hit. Nova network does
this a lot and is also slow enough to cause trouble, so this
patch attempts to address that for a few situations.

Related-bug: #1257626

Change-Id: Idc26776bf96ccfd9f50383e9d40aa47397d4e2cf

commit_message:
Fix description of ListSubnet

The help texts for both "neutron net-list" and "neutron subnet-list"
give the same text "List networks that belong to a given tenant."

Fix it so that subnet-list output the proper "subnet"

Change-Id: I0877b51ad10ac0e04b24effa7cbd1e412098e363
Partial-Bug: #1244618

(1 inline comment)

While I agree it seems strange that we are checking for the '@' char in 'ExternalDefault', the only thing to think about is whether we should be actually supporting what we did for Grizzly (which is to look for the user_id in the auth request).  I agree that was odd too, but it is what was in the release!

If we were making this change during Havana, I would say we actually should have three plugin methods 1) Grizzly compatible, 2) No domain - as your fix provides, and 3) Domain support, as provided by ExternalDomain.

Perhaps there is even merit of doing the above now - and making in backport potential? I'd like to bring a few others in to the discussion (e.g. gyee would made this change originally), so will add them to the reviewer list."}, {'account_id': 91, 'date': '2013-10-09 08:47:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Hi Henry. Thanks for your comments.

I have to recognize that I've overlooked all the v3 stuff until now, since we were using v2, so correct me if I am wrong or I am missing something.

For Grizzly v3 it was only possible to authenticate externally by passing a "password" or "token" method in the request, isn't it? i.e. there was no way to explicitly specify a "external" auth method (as per [1]). This is not always true, since there are authentication methods that do not need a username and password (for example, x.509), so [2] will fail for any of those methods.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/stable/grizzly/keystone/auth/controllers.py#L212
[2] https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/stable/grizzly/keystone/auth/controllers.py#L320

In Havana the external authentication was made pluggable, so that it is now possible to authenticate by using an external plugin, so all the information needed for authentication could be passed in the "external" part of the JSON document (i.e. the "domain").

I do agree that we should support a ExternalGrizzlyDeprecated plugin so that we are sure that people could still use it.'}, {'account_id': 5707, 'date': '2013-10-09 09:44:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

It's true there is no pluggable external ability....but REMOTE_USER is still supported in the controller, see: https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/stable/grizzly/keystone/auth/controllers.py#L320

I'm now thinking we should actively look at putting a change into Havana where we have the default plug in that does the same as Grizzly, with the two others (ExternalNoDomain and ExternalDomain) that match your fix."}, {'account_id': 1916, 'date': '2013-10-09 22:09:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this
